# Corpus data discipline

This rule loads whenever you're touching the pipeline's data — the same
discipline the study itself depends on for every number to be defensible.

- **`corpus/reports/*.json` and everything in `results/` are generated, not
  hand-edited.** They are produced by `corpus/run.mjs` and
  `corpus/build-results.mjs` respectively. If a number looks wrong, fix the
  manifest entry or file a critique — never hand-edit the output.
- **Never change an existing `corpus/manifest.json` entry's `commit` in
  place.** Add a new entry (or a dated note) instead — every claim in this
  study traces back to one pinned commit, and silently moving that target
  breaks that guarantee retroactively.
- **Write `analysis/ratings/<name>.md` before running the scanner on that
  repository, not after.** If a report already exists for a repo with no
  rating file yet, write the rating blind — without opening the report —
  or the comparison in `analysis/external-validity.md` is circular. See
  [METHODOLOGY.md](../../METHODOLOGY.md#blind-human-rating-q1-protocol).
- **`corpus/run.mjs` only clones and reads.** It must never `npm
  install`/`build`/`test` inside a scanned repository's checkout — that
  invariant is what makes it safe to point this pipeline at arbitrary
  third-party repositories.
